This paper involves game theory and decision-making in competitive environments, which are central topics in the field of computational game theory (cs.GT). The use of pre-commitment and strategic announcements also suggests a potential connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and modeling, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the consideration of team settings and alliances suggests a potential connection to social and information networks (cs.SI).
